# Absolute path aliases

Always import with the `@/` path alias. Never use relative imports (`./` or `../`).

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
import { useProjectChat } from "../../lib/hooks/useProjectChat";
import { Button } from "../ui/button";

// ✅ GOOD
import { useProjectChat } from "@/lib/hooks/useProjectChat";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
```

## Rules

- Resolve modules from `frontend/src` via `@/` (see `frontend/tsconfig.json` paths)
- Same-directory siblings still use `@/` — do not use `./foo`
- Do not introduce new relative import styles when editing existing files
